  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat oven to 400°F (200˚C). </step>
    <step num="1">In a bowl, mix together the salmon, chili sauce, and the scallions. </step>
    <step num="2">Place the fillets on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Spoon any leftover sauce on top of the salmon. </step>
    <step num="3">Bake for 12-15 minutes, until the salmon is cooked but still tender. </step>
    <step num="4">Enjoy! </step>
